        "created_at": "2021-06-29T23:20:11.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p><strong>N.V. Jacques Selosse Initial Champagne</strong>: Disgorged 12th of November 2019. Super-complex with notes of hazelnut cream, tart tatin, preserved lemon, smoke and flint. It is rich, full and powerful, with gentle nuttiness and loads of green apple. There\u2019s a vinous quality and a finish that is chewy and long.</p>\n<p><strong>N.V. Jacques Selosse Champagne Grand Cru Lieux-dits Extra Brut Ay La C\u00f4te Faron</strong>: Disgorged 19th February, 2020. Plenty of brown spice and baked apple to the aroma. There are red fruit and pastry notes too. It is rich and powerful, with all sorts of savoury nuance countering. It is gently frothy and finishes with great drive and energy.</p>",
